parameters.docstring: This parameter modifies the run register of the processor. Valid input: 1 = run, 0 = not run
parameters.label: Run Proc
parameters.name: run

parameters.docstring: This parameter sets the period of the grid to which the action releasing the run signal is aligned. Acceptable value range: [1, 65535], which is [20 ns, 1310700 ns].
parameters.label: Run Grid Period
parameters.name: run_grid_period

parameters.docstring: This parameter modifies the enable register of the processor. Make sure to enable first before running! Valid input: 1 = enable, 0 = disable
parameters.label: Enable Proc
parameters.name: enable

parameters.docstring: This parameter determines whether the execution of the instruction has finished. 1 = yes, 0 = no
parameters.label: Finished Execution
parameters.name: execution_done

parameters.docstring: This parameter determines whether the timing queue is empty. 1 = yes, 0 = no
parameters.label: Empty Timing Queue
parameters.name: timing_queue_empty

parameters.docstring: This parameter determines the number of append points to the vsm mask signal. The unit is 2.5 ns per point.
parameters.label: Number Append Points
parameters.name: num_append_pts

parameters.docstring: This parameter determines the extra output delay introduced for the DIO1 channel. It controls UHFQC1 to perform measurements on qubits 0, 2, 3, 5, and 6. The unit is 20ns.
parameters.label: Output Delay of DIO1, measuring qubit 0, 2, 3, 5 6
parameters.name: dio1_out_delay

parameters.docstring: This parameter determines the extra output delay introduced for the DIO1 channel. It controls UHFQC1 to perform measurements on qubits 1 and 4. The unit is 20ns.
parameters.label: Output Delay of DIO2, measuring qubit 1, 4
parameters.name: dio2_out_delay

parameters.docstring: This parameter determines the extra output delay introduced for the DIO3 channel. It controls AWG8 to perform flux control on all 7 qubits. The unit is 20ns.
parameters.label: Output Delay of DIO3, flux control all 7 qubits
parameters.name: dio3_out_delay

parameters.docstring: This parameter determines the extra output delay introduced for the DIO4 channel. It contains two microwave channels, which control qubits (0, 1) and (2, 3, 4), respectively. The unit is 20ns.
parameters.label: Output Delay of DIO4, microwave 1 (qubit 0, 1) and microwave 2 (qubit 2, 3, 4)
parameters.name: dio4_out_delay

parameters.docstring: This parameter determines the extra output delay introduced for the DIO5 channel. The unit is 20ns.

parameters.docstring: This parameter modifies the reset register of the QEC decoder submodule. Valid input: 1 = reset, 0 = idle

parameters.label: Enable QEC Decoder
parameters.name: qec_submodule_control_enable

parameters.docstring: This parameter modifies the initial values of ancilla qubit states for QEC. Decimal-encoded binary value representing one-hot encoding of ancilla qubit states.
parameters.label: Initialize QEC Decoder Ancillas
parameters.name: qec_submodule_init_aqb

parameters.docstring: This parameter modifies the data qubit readout type. Valid input: 0 = Z, 1 = X
